From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Pekka Vuorela <pekka.vuorela@jolla.com>
Date: Wed, 13 Aug 2025 09:13:27 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add back auhentication method 'any'

Originally introduced in our version of the 'auhtentication' element,
but briefly dropped when switching to upstream declaration.
It's not used in the data but sailfish ofono does have handling,
so keeping the declaration here as well.
---
 serviceproviders.2.dtd | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/serviceproviders.2.dtd b/serviceproviders.2.dtd
index 797653c2a..87876c371 100644
--- a/serviceproviders.2.dtd
+++ b/serviceproviders.2.dtd
@@ -107,7 +107,7 @@
 <!-- password required for authentication when starting a packet data session -->
 
 <!ELEMENT authentication EMPTY>
-<!ATTLIST authentication method (chap|pap) #REQUIRED>
+<!ATTLIST authentication method (chap|pap|any) #REQUIRED>
 <!-- method to use for authentication when starting a packet data session -->
 
 <!ELEMENT dns (#PCDATA)>
